    "markdown": "---\ntitle: \"Interactive E-Commerce Dashboard\"\ndescription: \"End-to-end data pipeline and interactive visualisations for e-commerce sales analysis.\"\nauthor: \"Shiva\"\ndate: \"2025-03-22\"\ncategories: [\"Data Analysis\", \"Plotly\", \"ETL\"]\nimage: \"../images/dashboard-cover.svg\"\nformat:\n  html:\n    toc: true\n    code-fold: true\n    code-tools: true\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nThis project demonstrates the creation of an interactive data dashboard for an e-commerce platform. We simulate processing a large transactional dataset, perform exploratory data analysis (EDA), and create interactive plots using `Plotly` directly within Quarto to provide actionable insights for stakeholders.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Data Processing and Cleaning\n\nFirst, we set up our environment and generate some realistic e-commerce data to work with.\n\n::: {#data-setup .cell message='false' execution_count=1}\n``` {.python .cell-code}\nimport pandas as pd\nimport numpy as np\nimport plotly.express as px\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta\n\n# Set seed for reproducibility\nnp.random.seed(101)\n\n# Generate 12 months of daily sales data\ndates = [datetime(2024, 1, 1) + timedelta(days=i) for i in range(365)]\nbase_sales = np.sin(np.linspace(0, 3.14, 365)) * 5000 + 10000\nnoise = np.random.normal(0, 800, 365)\ndaily_sales = base_sales + noise\n\n# Add seasonal spikes (e.g., Black Friday, Holidays)\ndaily_sales[320:330] += np.random.normal(8000, 1000, 10)  # Late Nov\ndaily_sales[345:355] += np.random.normal(6000, 800, 10)   # Pre-Xmas\n\ndf = pd.DataFrame({\n    'Date': dates,\n    'Revenue': daily_sales\n})\n\ndf['Month'] = df['Date'].dt.month_name()\ndf['Day_of_Week'] = df['Date'].dt.day_name()\n```\n:::\n\n\n## 2. Revenue Trends Over Time\n\nLet's look at the overall revenue trajectory across the year. The interactive features allow stakeholders to zoom into specific date ranges.\n\n::: {#cell-revenue-trend .cell execution_count=2}\n``` {.python .cell-code}\nfig = px.line(\n    df, \n    x='Date', \n    y='Revenue',\n    title='2024 Daily Revenue Forecast',\n    line_shape='spline',\n    render_mode='svg'\n)\n\nfig.update_traces(line_color='#0891b2', line_width=2)\nfig.update_layout(\n    xaxis_title=\"\",\n    yaxis_title=\"Revenue ($)\",\n    hovermode=\"x unified\"\n)\n\nfig.show()\n```\n\n::: {#revenue-trend .cell-output .cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div>            <script src=\"https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/mathjax/2.7.5/MathJax.js?config=TeX-AMS-MML_SVG\"></script><script>if (window.MathJax && window.MathJax.Hub && window.MathJax.Hub.Config) {window.MathJax.Hub.Config({SVG: {font: \"STIX-Web\"}});}</script>                <script>window.PlotlyConfig = {MathJaxConfig: 'local'};</script>\n        <script charset=\"utf-8\" src=\"https://cdn.plot.ly/plotly-3.5.0.min.js\" integrity=\"sha256-fHbNLP+GlIXN+efbQec78UkemUz3NJp7UmfGxC1tNxs=\" crossorigin=\"anonymous\"></script>                <div id=\"a9f33e4a-3f41-4672-91e4-92079556d644\" class=\"plotly-graph-div\" style=\"height:525px; width:100%;\"></div>            <script>                window.PLOTLYENV=window.PLOTLYENV || {};                                if (document.getElementById(\"a9f33e4a-3f41-4672-91e4-92079556d644\")) {                    Plotly.newPlot(                        \"a9f33e4a-3f41-4672-91e4-92079556d644\",                        [{\"hovertemplate\":\"Date=%{x}\\u003cbr\\u003eRevenue=%{y}\\u003cextra\\u003e\\u003c\\u002fextra\\u003e\",\"legendgroup\":\"\",\"line\":{\"color\":\"#0891b2\",\"dash\":\"solid\",\"shape\":\"spline\",\"width\":2},\"marker\":{\"symbol\":\"circle\"},\"mode\":\"lines\",\"name\":\"\",\"orientation\":\"v\",\"showlegend\":false,\"x\":[\"2024-01-01T00:00:00.000000000\",\"2024-01-02T00:00:00.000000000\",\"2024-01-03T00:00:00.000000000\",\"2024-01-04T00:00:00.000000000\",\"2024-01-05T00:00:00.000000000\",\"2024-01-06T00:00:00.000000000\",\"2024-01-07T00:00:00.000000000\",\"2024-01-08T00:00:00.000000000\",\"2024-01-09T00:0